{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/receive(messages:numMessages:flags:cancellable:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"receive"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"messages"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GInputMessage"},{"kind":"text","text":">!, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"numMessages"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"flags","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","text":"CancellableRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"messages"},{"type":"text","text":" must point to an array of "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputMessage"},{"type":"text","text":" structs and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"numMessages"},{"type":"text","text":" must be the length of this array. Each "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputMessage","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"contains a pointer to an array of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputVector"},{"text":" structs describing the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"buffers that the data received in each message will be written to. Using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"multiple ","type":"text"},{"code":"GInputVectors","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is more memory-efficient than manually copying data","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"out of a single buffer to multiple sources, and more system-call-efficient"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"than making multiple calls to ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_socket_receive()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", such as in scenarios where","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a lot of data packets need to be received (e.g. high-bandwidth video"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"streaming over RTP\/UDP)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"flags"},{"type":"text","text":" modify how all messages are received. The commonly available"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"arguments for this are available in the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketMsgFlags","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" enum, but the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"values there are the same as the system values, and the flags","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are passed in as-is, so you can pass in system-specific flags too. These","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"flags affect the overall receive operation. Flags affecting individual","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"messages are returned in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GInputMessage.flags"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The other members of ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputMessage","isActive":true},{"text":" are treated as described in its","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"documentation.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" the call will block until ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"numMessages"},{"type":"text","text":" have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"been received, or the end of the stream is reached."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":" the call will return up to ","type":"text"},{"code":"numMessages","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"without blocking, or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"wouldBlock"},{"text":" if no messages are queued in the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"operating system to be received.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In blocking mode, if "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket"},{"type":"text","text":" is positive and is reached before any"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"messages are received, "},{"code":"timedOut","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is returned, otherwise up to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"numMessages"},{"type":"text","text":" are returned. (Note: This is effectively the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behaviour of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MSG_WAITFORONE"},{"text":" with ","type":"text"},{"code":"recvmmsg()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To be notified when messages are available, wait for the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[in_](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/in_ condition. Note though that you may still receive","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"wouldBlock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_receive_messages()"},{"text":" even if you were","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"previously notified of a [in_](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/in_ condition."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the remote peer closes the connection, any messages queued in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operating system will be returned, and subsequent calls to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_receive_messages()"},{"text":" will return 0 (with no error set).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On error -1 is returned and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"error"},{"type":"text","text":" is set accordingly. An error will only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be returned if zero messages could be received; otherwise the number of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"messages successfully received before the error will be returned.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/socket\/receive(messages:nummessages:flags:cancellable:)"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/SocketProtocol-Implementations"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Receive multiple data messages from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"socket"},{"type":"text","text":" in one go.  This is the most"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"complicated and fully-featured version of this call. For easier use, see","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_socket_receive()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"g_socket_receive_from()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_receive_message()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:3GIO14SocketProtocolPAAE7receive8messages11numMessages5flags11cancellableSiSpySo14_GInputMessageVGSg_S2iAA14CancellableRefVSgtKF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO6SocketC","symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"GIO","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"receive","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"messages"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GInputMessage"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"numMessages","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"flags","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","text":"CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}],"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"role":"symbol","title":"receive(messages:numMessages:flags:cancellable:)"},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Socket/SocketProtocol-Implementations":{"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socket\/socketprotocol-implementations","role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/SocketProtocol-Implementations","kind":"article","abstract":[],"title":"SocketProtocol Implementations","type":"topic"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableRef":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableref","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" allows operations to be cancelled."}],"title":"CancellableRef"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Socket/receive(messages:numMessages:flags:cancellable:)":{"title":"receive(messages:numMessages:flags:cancellable:)","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socket\/receive(messages:nummessages:flags:cancellable:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket\/receive(messages:numMessages:flags:cancellable:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"receive"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"messages"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"GInputMessage","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"numMessages"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"flags","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","text":"CancellableRef"},{"text":"?) ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Receive multiple data messages from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"socket"},{"type":"text","text":" in one go.  This is the most"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"complicated and fully-featured version of this call. For easier use, see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_receive()"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_receive_from()"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_receive_message()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/InputVector":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputVector","title":"InputVector","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/inputvector","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Structure used for scatter\/gather data input."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You generally pass in an array of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GInputVectors"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and the operation will store the read data starting in the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"first buffer, switching to the next as needed.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"InputVector"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"InputVector","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Socket":{"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Socket"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Socket","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socket","abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"code":"GSocket","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a low-level networking primitive. It is a more or less"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"direct mapping of the BSD socket API in a portable GObject based API."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It supports both the UNIX socket implementations and winsock2 on Windows.","type":"text"}],"title":"Socket","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Socket","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/SocketMsgFlags":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketMsgFlags","abstract":[{"text":"Flags used in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_receive_message()"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_socket_send_message()"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The flags listed in the enum are some commonly available flags, but the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"values used for them are the same as on the platform, and any other flags"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are passed in\/out as is. So to use a platform specific flag, just include","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the right system header and pass in the flag."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SocketMsgFlags"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socketmsgflags","title":"SocketMsgFlags","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SocketMsgFlags","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/InputMessage":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"InputMessage","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputMessage","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/inputmessage","title":"InputMessage","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"InputMessage","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Structure used for scatter\/gather data input when receiving multiple"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"messages or packets in one go. You generally pass in an array of empty","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GInputVectors"},{"text":" and the operation will use all the buffers as if they","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"were one buffer, and will set "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"bytes_received"},{"type":"text","text":" to the total number of bytes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"received across all ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GInputVectors"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"}}}